# HailGuard — environment overview
# ---------------------------------
# Each app reads its OWN env file (this root file is documentation only):
#   - mobile/.env            (Expo Driver Hub)        → see mobile/.env.example
#   - admin/.env.local       (Next.js Fleet Portal)   → see admin/.env.example
#
# Supabase has no app-level env file: apply SQL via the dashboard or
# `supabase` CLI (migrations in supabase/migrations + supabase/seed.sql).
#
# Required everywhere:
#   SUPABASE URL + ANON KEY        (Supabase → Project Settings → API)
#   SERVICE_ROLE KEY               (admin only, server-side)
#
# Optional / future:
#   MAP_TILE_URL / ATTRIBUTION     (admin dashboard map; defaults to OSM)
#   PAYFAST / STRIPE keys          (when replacing the stub payment provider)
